## Self-Forming Return Medium

Lightning Holder exists first as a prepared system.

Before the strike, it only creates the initial conditions: water geometry, ultrasonic structure, detection readiness, mechanical stabilization, and a local active point.

The full medium does not exist yet.

It is created by the lightning strike itself.

When the discharge enters the system, it transforms water into steam, pressure, ionized mist, aerosol, and plasma-like activity. These products form a temporary cloud-like environment around the system.

This new environment becomes a return medium.

Part of the secondary wave may be reflected, damped, delayed, or redirected back into the active region instead of escaping immediately.

In this way, the first lightning event creates the conditions for its own continuation.

Lightning Holder is therefore not only a prepared receiver. It is a system that becomes more active after impact, because the impact itself generates the medium that can hold, return, and slow the decay of the event.
